This paper deals with the segmentation of MRI images using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural networks for this task also suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a hypercolumns fully convolutional network, which is a type of neural network architecture commonly used in computer vision tasks such as object detection and segmentation. This suggests that neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) may also be relevant sub-categories.
